                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18411129-name-1286" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-1286" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-1286" type="surname" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18411129-name-1286" type="given" value="LEWIS"></interp>LEWIS LEWIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an ironmonger, and live in Crawford-street—the prisoner worked for me occasionally—I sent him into the front area to repair a cistern, on the 2nd of December—he came up and asked me for some money to get some compo'—I saw a bit of leaden-pipe in his cloth—I took it out and found it was mine—I then missed it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. I did not intend to take it away. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. It was wrapped up in his cloth with some tools—I said, "What have you there?"—he said, "My tools"—I then found this—he said, "Pray, forgive me, it is my first time."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">JURY</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where was the lead kept? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> In the front kitchen, which was used as a warehouse—he was working as a bricklayer—he is not a plumber.</p>
